@csosto-pk [RFC 3279](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc3279/) and [RFC 8419](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc8419/) did not, but that's why we ended up with [RFC 7468](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc7468/) much later for RFC 3279.  You'll note nothing has been done for RFC 8419.

The curve25519 and x448 crowd went for just including it all in one, see [RFC 8410](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/rfc8410/).

I went for the all in one approach. I am however **_NOT_** wed to this section. I just think that it doesn't really hurt to include it.

```suggestion
